ncxmms2 uses C++11 features, so you need at least GCC 4.6 or Clang 3.1.

    Packages needed to build on Ubuntu (tested on Ubuntu 12.04):
git
build-essential
cmake
libboost-dev
libncurses5-dev
libncursesw5-dev
libglib2.0-dev
libxmmsclient++-dev
libxmmsclient++-glib-dev

    Build process is straightforward:
$ git clone git://github.com/pkunavin/ncxmms2.git
$ cd ncxmms2
$ cmake -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=/usr .
$ make
    And if you need system wide install:
$ make install

    Also there is a PKGBUILD for Arch Linux, see http://aur.archlinux.org/packages.php?ID=52383
